questions.questionText:
Section 142 of the Water Act (Cap. 372) gives the Cabinet Secretary for Water, Sanitation and Irrigation, the power to make regulations to provide for water harvesting and storage. The Act also establishes the National Water Harvesting and Storage Authority headed by a Chief Executive Officer (CEO). As a senior legal counsel in the National Water Harvesting and Storage Authority, the Chief Executive Officer of the Authority has requested you to prepare draft regulations on water harvesting and storage for onward transmission to and approval by the Cabinet Secretary. The draft regulations to provide for roof-based water harvesting, land-based rainwater harvesting, rainwater harvesting by agricultural establishments, storm water run-off and provision for technical and capacity building support. The new regulations provide for further functions of the Authority which includes: undertake on behalf of the national government the development of national public water works for water resources storage and flood control; collect information for the formulation by the Cabinet Secretary of the national water resources storage and flood control strategies; implement and maintain a website, which shall provide technical and capacity building support to enable compliance with these regulations; development of water harvesting policy; and enforcement of water harvesting strategies. The new regulations also revoke the current regulations enacted in 2021. Specifically, the CEO indicates that the draft regulations should clearly set out the following aspects: 
i. Citation;
ii. Purpose;
iii. Functions of the Authority;
iv. Roof-based rainwater may be harvested for use through a filter into a storage tank;
v. Any building constructed and to be utilized as an institutional facility, place of employment, manufacturing or industrial establishment, commercial establishment or place for service of customers, shall have its roof adequately guttered for collecting rain water or may have a ground catchment for purposes of collecting rain water pursuant to these regulations;
vi. Land-based rainwater harvesting shall be done using the appropriate ground water recharge structures;
vii. The National Water Harvesting and Storage Authority shall implement and maintain a website which shall provide technical and capacity building support to enable compliance with these regulations;
viii. Every agricultural establishment using water resources for irrigation purposes shall implement water harvesting and storage measures capable of storing flood water;
ix. Rainwater from the roof of the buildings with tiled or sloped roof and flat roofs may be harvested using sized gutters;
x. A county government shall put in place measures to ensure that provision is made for planning, managing, and improving drainage services and storm water run-off collection within its area of jurisdiction;
xi. Revocation of current Regulations enacted in 2021.
Prepare the draft regulations. (10 Marks)
